parameters.description: Maximum phytoplankton growth rate at reference temperature
parameters.enhanced_semantic_description: Maximum phytoplankton intrinsic growth rate at T_ref=20°C (day^-1). This is the base rate that will be modulated by temperature.

parameters.description: Half-saturation constant for nutrient uptake by phytoplankton
parameters.enhanced_semantic_description: Half-saturation nutrient concentration for phytoplankton uptake (g C m^-3)

parameters.description: Maximum nutrient uptake efficiency at low nutrient concentrations (logit-transformed, will be bounded 0-1)
parameters.enhanced_semantic_description: Maximum phytoplankton nutrient uptake efficiency under nutrient-limited conditions (proportion 0-1); logit value of 1.735 transforms to ~0.85 (85% efficiency). This represents luxury uptake capacity when nutrients are scarce. Higher than average efficiency to capture upregulation of uptake machinery at low nutrient availability.

parameters.description: Half-saturation constant for nutrient uptake efficiency response
parameters.enhanced_semantic_description: Nutrient concentration at which uptake efficiency is half-maximal (g C m^-3). Controls how rapidly efficiency decreases with increasing nutrient availability. Should be on same order as K_N to create meaningful efficiency variation across typical nutrient ranges. Lower values indicate efficiency drops rapidly with nutrients; higher values indicate efficiency remains high across broader nutrient range.

parameters.description: Maximum zooplankton grazing rate at reference temperature
parameters.enhanced_semantic_description: Maximum zooplankton grazing rate on phytoplankton at T_ref=20°C (day^-1). This is the base rate that will be modulated by temperature.

parameters.description: Half-saturation constant for zooplankton grazing on phytoplankton
parameters.enhanced_semantic_description: Half-saturation phytoplankton concentration for zooplankton grazing (g C m^-3)

parameters.description: Zooplankton assimilation efficiency (logit-transformed, will be bounded 0-1)
parameters.enhanced_semantic_description: Zooplankton assimilation efficiency of ingested phytoplankton (0-1); logit value of -0.4 transforms to ~0.40 (40% efficiency), consistent with marine zooplankton growth efficiency

parameters.description: Phytoplankton mortality rate at reference temperature
parameters.enhanced_semantic_description: Phytoplankton natural mortality rate at T_ref=20°C (day^-1). This is the base rate that will be modulated by temperature.

parameters.description: Zooplankton linear mortality rate at reference temperature (natural death and senescence)
parameters.enhanced_semantic_description: Zooplankton natural mortality rate from senescence and disease at T_ref=20°C (day^-1), excluding predation. This is the base rate that will be modulated by temperature.

parameters.description: Zooplankton quadratic mortality coefficient representing density-dependent predation by higher trophic levels
parameters.enhanced_semantic_description: Quadratic mortality coefficient for zooplankton representing predation by implicit higher trophic levels (fish, carnivorous zooplankton). This density-dependent term (m_Z2 * Z^2) captures predator-prey encounter rates and prevents unrealistic zooplankton blooms. Typical values 0.01-0.5 based on marine NPZ models.

parameters.description: Nutrient recycling fraction from dead organic matter (logit-transformed, will be bounded 0-1)
parameters.enhanced_semantic_description: Fraction of dead biomass recycled to nutrients (0-1); logit value of 0.0 transforms to 0.50 (50% recycling), middle of typical range 30-80%

parameters.description: Surface light intensity (incoming solar radiation)
parameters.enhanced_semantic_description: Surface photosynthetically active radiation (PAR) intensity. Typical values: 100-500 μmol photons m^-2 s^-1 for average oceanic conditions, up to 2000 for peak midday tropical conditions. Starting value of 400 represents moderate light conditions.

parameters.description: Half-saturation constant for light-limited phytoplankton growth
parameters.enhanced_semantic_description: Light intensity at which phytoplankton growth is half-maximal. Typical values: 20-100 μmol photons m^-2 s^-1 for marine phytoplankton, varying by species and adaptation state. Lower values indicate shade-adapted species, higher values indicate high-light adapted species.

parameters.description: Background light attenuation coefficient (water clarity/turbidity)
parameters.enhanced_semantic_description: Background light attenuation due to water molecules, dissolved organic matter, and non-phytoplankton particles. Typical values: 0.02-0.05 m^-1 for clear oceanic water, 0.1-0.5 m^-1 for turbid coastal waters. Starting value of 0.04 m^-1 represents moderately clear oceanic conditions.

parameters.description: Phytoplankton self-shading coefficient (chlorophyll-specific light attenuation)
parameters.enhanced_semantic_description: Specific light attenuation coefficient per unit phytoplankton biomass, representing self-shading effects. Typical values: 0.02-0.05 m^2 (g C)^-1 based on chlorophyll-specific attenuation and carbon:chlorophyll ratios. Higher values indicate stronger self-shading (e.g., larger cells, higher pigment content).

parameters.description: Mixed layer depth
parameters.enhanced_semantic_description: Depth of the oceanic mixed layer where phytoplankton are actively mixed. Typical values: 20-100 m depending on season and location. Shallow mixed layers (20-40 m) occur in summer stratification, deep mixed layers (100-200 m) occur in winter mixing. Starting value of 50 m represents intermediate conditions.

parameters.description: Water temperature
parameters.enhanced_semantic_description: Ambient water temperature in the mixed layer (°C). Typical oceanic range: -2°C (polar) to 30°C (tropical). Temperature modulates all biological rates via exponential temperature dependence. Can be constant or time-varying to represent seasonal cycles. Starting value of 15°C represents temperate ocean conditions.

parameters.description: Reference temperature for rate parameters
parameters.enhanced_semantic_description: Reference temperature at which base rate parameters (r_P, g_max, m_P, m_Z) are defined (°C). Standard value is 20°C following Eppley (1972) and most marine biogeochemical models. All rates are scaled relative to this temperature using exponential temperature dependence.

parameters.description: Temperature coefficient for phytoplankton growth
parameters.enhanced_semantic_description: Temperature sensitivity coefficient for phytoplankton growth rate (°C^-1). Value of 0.063 from Eppley (1972) corresponds to Q10 ≈ 1.88 (growth increases ~88% per 10°C). This is the most widely used value in marine ecosystem models. Lower values (0.03-0.05) represent cold-adapted species; higher values (0.07-0.10) represent warm-adapted species.

parameters.description: Temperature coefficient for zooplankton grazing
parameters.enhanced_semantic_description: Temperature sensitivity coefficient for zooplankton grazing rate (°C^-1). Value of 0.069 corresponds to Q10 ≈ 2.0 (grazing doubles per 10°C). Heterotrophs typically have slightly higher temperature sensitivity than autotrophs due to metabolic costs. Range 0.04-0.12 encompasses variation across zooplankton taxa and sizes.

parameters.description: Temperature coefficient for mortality and remineralization
parameters.enhanced_semantic_description: Temperature sensitivity coefficient for mortality and bacterial remineralization processes (°C^-1). Value of 0.069 corresponds to Q10 ≈ 2.0 (rates double per 10°C). Bacterial decomposition and metabolic mortality are temperature-sensitive. Similar to grazing coefficient as both represent heterotrophic processes.

parameters.description: Log-scale standard deviation for nutrient observations
parameters.enhanced_semantic_description: Logarithm of nutrient observation standard deviation (log g C m^-3)

parameters.description: Log-scale standard deviation for phytoplankton observations
parameters.enhanced_semantic_description: Logarithm of phytoplankton observation standard deviation (log g C m^-3)

parameters.description: Log-scale standard deviation for zooplankton observations
parameters.enhanced_semantic_description: Logarithm of zooplankton observation standard deviation (log g C m^-3)

parameters.description: Time vector for observations
parameters.enhanced_semantic_description: Observation time points in days

parameters.description: Observed nutrient concentration
parameters.enhanced_semantic_description: Observed nutrient concentration in mixed layer (g C m^-3)

parameters.description: Observed phytoplankton concentration
parameters.enhanced_semantic_description: Observed phytoplankton biomass concentration (g C m^-3)

parameters.description: Observed zooplankton concentration
parameters.enhanced_semantic_description: Observed zooplankton biomass concentration (g C m^-3)
